Thursday, 28 November 2013


[sebaygo1]


Show Description

From the Infowars web site :: On this November 28, Thanksgiving Day broadcast of the Alex Jones Show, Alex talks with Patrick Wood, editor of The August Forecast and Review, about the emerging technocracy. Mr. Wood worked with the late Antony Sutton on a highly regarded two-volume book, Trilaterals Over Washington, that became a standard reference on global elitism. Alex also talks with F. Michael Maloof, staff writer for WND and a former senior security policy analyst in the office of the Secretary of Defense. Mr. Maloof talks about Obama's purge of the military. Alex talks about Obamacare, the NSA and other topics with computer programmer and founder of McAfee, Inc., John McAfee.

NOTE: Today's show consists entirely of previously aired material from broadcasts in recent weeks.

This upload is the Prison Planet "members' edit," which has the commercials during scheduled breaks removed and the entire show in one MP3 file.
